This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Combinatory Category Grammar (CCG) supertagging, which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks, which are a popular tool in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a dynamic window approach, which involves attention mechanisms, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The use of dropout is also mentioned, which is a common regularization technique in neural networks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with sentence-level tasks, which are often related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) in NLP.
